Cusp is reclined, wide (from upper to lower margin) and straight, with keels developed along the anterior (upper) and posterior (lower) margins. A weak, median, longitudinal carina is developed on the inner side of the cusp. Occasionally, the carina may be distinct. Basal margin is weakly rounded or straight. A distinct keel is developed on the upper margin. Anterior margin is rounded or weakly rounded (convex). Angle A (
Fig. 3
) between the cusp and upper margin of the base is ca 30° (mean) with a standard deviation of 4.3 (
Fig. 5B
), and mean ratio between length of the free upper margin and the free cusp is ca 0.25 with a standard deviation of 0.05.
